{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "scholarscan-backend-api-collection",
		"name": "ScholarScan Backend API",
		"description": "Production-ready Postman collection for the ScholarScan assessment system backend API.\n\n## Overview\nScholarScan is an automated answer-sheet assessment system that uses OCR, NLP, and a Groq-backed LLM service to evaluate student answers against model answers.\n\n## Supported Modes\n- **Manual single-question assessment**: Upload an image of a student answer along with a model answer for immediate synchronous grading.\n- **Async multi-question assessment**: Upload an image or PDF answer file (and optionally a question paper) for background processing of multiple questions.\n\n## Async Assessment Flow\n1. Submit an assessment via `POST /api/assess` (returns `task_id` with HTTP 202).\n2. Stream real-time progress via `GET /api/progress/stream/{task_id}` (SSE endpoint).\n3. Poll or fetch the final result via `GET /api/task/{task_id}/result`.\n4. Browse assessment history via `GET /api/results`.\n\n## Configuration\nSet the collection variables before running requests. At minimum, update `manualImagePath`, `answerFilePath`, and `questionFilePath` to point to real files on your machine.\n\nFor auto-reference generation, start the backend with `GROQ_API_KEY`, optionally override `GROQ_BASE_URL`, and confirm `GET /api/health` reports `llm_configured: true`.\n\nDefault Groq settings reflected here:\n- `groqBaseUrl`: `https://api.groq.com/openai/v1`\n- `llmModel`: `llama-3.3-70b-versatile`\n\n## Upload Limits\n- Maximum file size: 16 MB\n- Allowed extensions: jpg, jpeg, png, pdf",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
